  <front>
   <head>ON A YOUNG LADY, WHO ASKED A NECKLACE OF A GENTLEMAN's HAIR, AND WAS REFUSED</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And is it thus, Miranda cried,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And am I then by him denied,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Alas my heart is sore;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Why did I make the fond request?</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Why not conceal it in my breast,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">As I had done before?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I know not how he spoke so fair,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I wish'd to have his yellow hair,</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And wear it round my neck;</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But, O! it hurt his gentle mind,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Such boldness in my sex to find,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Then what could I expect.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
